nt in the repository, so ownership of that result is unclear."],"impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","confidence":"high"}},"issues":[{"dimension":"high_level_elegance","identifier":"catch_all_utils_owns_multiple_layers","summary":"One shared utils module mixes transport, domain rules, and presentation concerns","related_files":["nba_pbp_utils.py","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["`nba_pbp_utils.py` contains HTTP access (`fetch_playbyplay_payload`), dataframe construction (`actions_to_dataframe`), possession/domain helpers (`build_valid_possessions`, `count_defensive_fouls`, `infer_team_score_side`), and output formatting (`format_output_preview`) in one module.","Each top-level script imports a different slice of that same module as its main dependency, so developers have to treat `nba_pbp_utils.py` as a catch-all ownership boundary rather than a domain-specific API."],"suggestion":"Split `nba_pbp_utils.py` into a small package with explicit modules such as `data_source.py`, `pbp_transform.py`, `possession_model.py`, and `reporting.py`, then make scripts depend on those narrower modules or a thin public pipeline API.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"script_first_structure"},{"dimension":"high_level_elegance","identifier":"pipeline_logic_scattered_across_entry_scripts","summary":"Core WMI pipeline is reimplemented across peer scripts instead of owned by one subsystem","related_files":["build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py","step2_build_possessions.py"],"evidence":["`build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py` computes possession rows, score context, foul flags, and WMI variables directly in one script.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` separately rebuilds possession tables and WMI variables for a season, while `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` uses a different path that skips possession tables and derives a foul vector from raw actions.","Because these scripts are peers at the repo root, the top-level structure suggests each file owns its own version of the workflow instead of exposing one predictable subsystem for 'build possessions', 'derive WMI inputs', and 'aggregate results'."],"suggestion":"Create a dedicated pipeline package that owns the stages explicitly, for example `pipeline/ingest.py`, `pipeline/possessions.py`, `pipeline/wmi_inputs.py`, and `pipeline/aggregations.py`, then reduce the current scripts to thin CLI wrappers over that shared flow.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"script_first_structure"},{"dimension":"high_level_elegance","identifier":"docs_and_outputs_do_not_map_to_clear_entrypoints","summary":"Top-level docs describe outputs and stages that the repository cannot clearly regenerate","related_files":["README.md","Plan for WMI - Ryan Kalfus (2026).md","Definitions for NBA Analytics Research - Ryan Kalfus (2026).md","nba-whistle-project-log.md"],"evidence":["`README.md` only describes the possession builder's current status, so it does not tell a new developer where the broader WMI pipeline lives or which scripts are authoritative.","The plan and definitions list current outputs including `wmi_rawseason_2025_26_summary_asof_2026_03_01.csv`, but the repository has no matching production script for 2025-26 generation; only 2024-25 and 2010-11-to-2023-24 season scripts exist.","`nba-whistle-project-log.md` records the 2025-26 summary as a project artifact, which makes the absence of a clear owning entrypoint more confusing rather than clarifying ownership."],"suggestion":"Add a real top-level project map in `README.md` that names the authoritative pipeline stages and entrypoints, and either add the missing 2025-26 producer script or move generated outputs under a documented `outputs/` area with metadata showing which script produced each file.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"script_first_structure"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["The repository is organized around chronological script additions and generated artifacts instead of stable domain packages.","Shared behavior was centralized into one helper module without a matching architectural split between transport, parsing, modeling, and reporting.","Documentation evolved as project notes/logs, but the top-level contract was never consolidated into one authoritative map of code ownership and entrypoints."],"likely_symptoms":["catch_all_utils_owns_multiple_layers","pipeline_logic_scattered_across_entry_scripts","docs_and_outputs_do_not_map_to_clear_entrypoints"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}
